strings.string: \rStriiiike three.\r
\rThe way is now open.\r
\rProject Darwin researches and produces mutants to make...\r
\r...the shattered world safe again for all life.\r
\rThe researchers, led by Irwin John Finster, have created life that has adapted to the world.\r
\rDarwin produces only useful life in its labs.\r
\rDarwin was built by concerned Scientists after the nuclear war. It is the salvation of the world.\r
\rCell 2: Academic data\r
\rDo you wish to take the cowardly way out?\r
\rCell 1: General Information\r
\rThis is simple math, you need no help.\r
\r"Aargghh!" Finster screams in rage. "You will not escape traps in the future like that."\r
\rProject Darwin has always had research and Education as its highest priorities.\r
\rOnly the covert nature of the work at Darwin prevented the staff from winning a Nobel Prize for genetics.\r
\rOur pride has been the students we have trained. All found Darwin an experience that changed them.\r
\rWhat is the difference between a duck?\r
\rWhat is the sound of one hand clapping?\r
\rCogito Ergo Sum.\r
\rWhat is the union of one?\r
\r"Sugar and Spice and everything malignant."\r
\rEach step from birth is toward death.\r
\rJust because you are paranoid does not mean they are not out to get you.\r
\rKnow Thyself.\r
\rSizzling balls of rainbow hues swirl around you and tear at you. You can go no further.\r
\rYou feel as if your body is utterly drained of energy and you can move no further.\r

\r"What are you doing here? I am dead, am I not? How are you in my mind when I am dead? I must be in your mind. I am in your mind. And him. He is a friend you remember from long ago. He lurked beneath your bed."\r
\rYou see a signpost ahead. It says, "Danger! Unprepared rangers will not survive."\r
\r"Scary brute, is he not? And you could never kill him then either, could you?"\r
\r"Pah! I tire of you. Be gone!"\r
\r"WRONG! The correct answer is 20."\r
\r"You cheated, ha, ha, HA! Don't play tricks on me in my mind."\r
\r"No fair, that's out of bounds."\r
"Are you still here? This is private. Only I am allowed further."\r
\r"You didn't think this would be that easy, did you?"\r
FINSTER
\rAfter Finster's death, thick cobwebs clog the lifeless landscape preventing further progress.\r
\r"Kibbles and bits, kibbles and bits. I'm gunna carve you into kibbles and bits!"\r
\r"Look before you leap! I want to eat your brain!"\r
\r"Cue ball in the corner pocket! See, I call my shots!"\r
\r"This could be your big break!"\r
\r"I was a tad irrational back there, wasn't I? I promise it will not happen again."\r
\rWebs of Deceit, steel strong yet transparent, block you.\r
"Oh, I guess I lied about being rational. Mad of me, is it not? And I thought of it as a little white lie."\r
"You cannot be here. Nothing will get you beyond this point."\r
NOTHING
\r"I am a liar. I would say nothing to help you."\r
\r"Bet you thought that was easy, hee, hee, hee."\r
\r"Did you know baseball history was a passion of mine? Here, I create a dream game. Or, in your case, a nightmare."\r
\r"The pitcher, a shimmering hologram of Christy Matthews rears back and pitches."\r
\rA bat materializes in your hand and you connect with the pitch!\r
\rYou hit a single.\r
\rYou hit a double!\r
\rYou slam a triple!!\r
\rYou tag a home run!!!\r
\r"The runner takes a lead..."\r
\r"Swing and a miss."\r
\r"Strike 1, ha!"\r
\r"Strike 2, hee, hee"\r
\r"Yer out! To the showers with you!"\r
\r...and is gunned down trying to steal! You're done. Into the showers with you!\r
\r"...and manages to steal a base!"\r
"So, you think yourself good at baseball, eh? Then who won the 1936 world series?"\r
NEW YORK YANKEES
\rAn azure image of Joe McCarthy shakes his head and spits in the corner. "Why play you when I have Lou Gehrig?"\r
\rMcCarthy spits again. "OK, kid, I'll give you another chance."\r
\rMcCarthy frowns. "Kid, if you can't tell me why I should play you, I just won't be able to put you in."\r
\rSolid walls of smoky silicon hem you in. Throughout them you see the delicate lines of circuitry.\r
\rYou shatter the silicon wall and scatter bits of it everywhere, leaving a jagged hole in the wall.\r
\rThis silicon wall bends slightly under the pressure of your touch. It appears more fragile than strong.\r
\rFinster's voice mocks you. "Come now, you can try harder. You are a Ranger, are you not?"\r
Standing before you is an android. A voice booms from his chest. "There you are." He sounds like Finster!\r
Finster pops up in front of you and thumbs back the hammer on the largest pistol you've ever seen!\r
"I begged you to kill me, now you create us!" To your horror a pair of Finsters arise in the corners.\r
"Please, I beg of you, kill me. I cannot live insane in my own mind!" Finster looks pitiful.\r
\rBroken pieces of silicon crackle beneath your feet.\r
\rYou hear haunting mechanical laughter ring out. "Clothes make the man, eh Ranger?" You find no body!\r
\rAs you pick up the jug Finster's voice grates across your nerves. "Take it, Ranger, use it to catch up your blood."\r
\r"New games now, Ranger. I play for blood."\r
\rThe plastic face drips with black blood. The eyes open, the head speaks. "April 15, 1912 I killed a ship."\r\r"What am I?"\r
ICEBERG
\rYou see another signpost ahead. It says, "Last chance! There will be no turning back if you proceed much further."\r
IRWIN FINSTER

\r"I am impressed, Ranger. You have come further than anyone before you, including my creator. You are a noble foe. However, you are only human. I offer a choice. Your life for those of your comrades. West for you, east to kill them."\r
\rIt is done.\r
IRWIN J FINSTER
\r"Fool, I cannot be trusted! You have just doomed your friends in addition to yourself. The exits are all trapped!\rYou'll never leave Project Darwin alive!"\r
\rDamned if you
do.\r
don't.\r
\r"You made your choice, now die with it!"\r
IRWIN J. FINSTER
\r"Look, the EEG is flat! The android won!" you hear voices say. There is worry in the voices of your friends.\r
\r"No, look, there is a slight wave on the scope. Come on, Ranger, fight for your life!" Hope enters the voices.\r
\rDoubt creeps into a voice. "The wave was probably just a jolt in the line. We're talking brain dead here."\r
\r"No, hey look! The signal is getting stronger. Fight, Ranger, damn you, fight it!"\r
\r"The wave is going flat again. The android is winning."\r
\r"Look, the wave is back, and is stronger than ever. Go, Ranger, go. Give it hell!"\r
\r"So close, but I think we're losing the battle. Damn, we can't do anything to help. Fight!"\r
\rFinster's voice is absolutely frantic! "No! You cannot be here still. Stay back, get out, leave!"\r
\rFinster curses! "Get back, leave here, begone or I will sear the flesh from your bones!"\r
\rThe area around you bursts into flame, but you leap clear before you can be engulfed by the conflagration.\r
\rThe void explodes in flame and you are caught in it before you stumble on.\r
\rYou notice a shiny glimmering ahead that hints at a trap so you leap over the next 10 feet and continue.\r
\rSESSION TERMINATED...THANK YOU\r
\rNothing happens here.\r
\rThe ceiling above you explodes in a hail of swirling razor edged steel blades. Finster's laughter echoes from the walls...\r
\r...and is choked off as you duck and twist your way free of the death storm!\r
\r...and shrieks a hideous accompaniment to the sounds of blades ripping and tearing at you.\r
Finster stands there. It is a twisted, warped and torn plassteel imitation of a man. Screaming, it charges.\r
\rFinster's voice is a harsh buzzing croak. "Do you hear me, Ranger? This is the end. I will finish you. I will crush you. You, too, will die!"\r
IRWIN JOHN FINSTER

\rThe android body twitches and gushes black fluid from a thousand wounds. "Use the pass well. Without it you will never get the things you need from Sleeper One. And without the weapons you will never destroy the places that spawned me or the robots that scour all life from the face of your world!" With a *CRACK* and spark, the android is dead!\r
ZERO
\rYou realize the pit in the center is not bottomless, but is a way out.\r
